#### Getting Started

First load the seed and CSS files, if you haven't yet.

```html
<script src="<%= @getCdnSeed() %>"></script>
<link href="<%= @getBootstrapCSS() %>" rel="stylesheet"></link>
```

Then initialize AlloyUI and load the Ace Editor module.

``` javascript
AUI().use(
  'aui-test',
  function(Y) {
    // code goes here
  }
);
```

---

<div class="section-number"><span class="blue-circle white">2</span></div>

#### Using Test

Create an HTML element for the Test.

```html
<div id="myTest"></div>
```

Now create a new instance of Test with the newly created element.

```javascript
AUI().use(
  'aui-test',
  function(A) {
    new A.AceEditor(
      {
        boundingBox: '#myTest'
      }
    ).render();
  }
);
```

